<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-15024] Don&apos;t try to cancel 2i compactions when starting anticompaction</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-15024</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we start an anticompaction we cancel ongoing compactions, &lt;tt&gt;runWithCompactionsDisabled&lt;/tt&gt; always cancels compactions for secondary index cfs:es, this causes problem since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14935&quot; title=&quot;PendingAntiCompaction should be more judicious in the compactions it cancels&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-14935&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-14935&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; since we check for range intersection which will fail since 2i sstables are LocalPartitioner.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
